Contract performance management:
Practical Completion under this contract is reached at the successful completion of:
• the Feeder Station FIT
• close out of the critical defects
• issuing of the redline mark ups
• issuing a certificate stating the installation is fit and safe to energise
• Cold Commissioning, Hot Commissioning/Energisation & Final Commissioning (including on loads)

As a precondition to Practical Completion being achieved the SFC Contractor must, without limiting any other obligation of the SFC Contractor shall thoroughly check all installations, Equipment, and services to ensure that performance is correct and in order. This includes the following tasks on any building/Equipment deliverables:
o Adjust all moving parts, doors, windows, etc., examine and clear all drains and gutters, ensure all bolts and screws are tight, and test all services are working, to the approval of the Purchaser
o Remove all render, carelessly applied material and other spots on metal sashes, box sections, walls, table type surfaces, cabinets, equipment boxes, service ducts, conduits and other equipment surfaces
o Clean, wash and dry all floor areas and concrete slab areas
o Remove all paint spots from floors and walls, rubbish and building materials from the site area and the cleanliness of all ducts, cupboards, conduits
o Check all cable identifiers, labels, tags, etc.
o Clean out all ducts, cabinets, distribution boards, switchboards, cupboards, etc.
o Provide a certificate stating the installation is fit for service and safe to energise.
